The paper proposes a deep learning framework for analyzing task-based fMRI data, which involves processing large amounts of data and leveraging the processing power of multiple GPUs in a distributed fashion. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, given the focus on deep learning and image analysis, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
